# Phase D — the universal resource path. namec() resolves an open
# through the calling process's Pgrp mount table to a Chan, dispatching
# devtab[] for a local cdev and mountrpc (9P T-messages) for a mounted
# 9P server — the SAME Chan type and the SAME read/write/close
# interface for both. vfs_open routes cdev + 9P-mounted opens through
# namec and installs ONE FD_CHAN_MARK fd; vfs_read/write/close dispatch
# FD_CHAN_MARK fds back into namec_read/write/close. This is the Plan 9
# inversion: the dozen FD_<NAME>_MARK special-cases stop being the
# substrate and become a single chan-backed path. The legacy
# FD_<NAME>_MARK arms below stay as a non-regressing fallback for any
# call site (e.g. `#X` aliases) not yet routed through namec.
